articles.title: Hong Kong stocks mirror Wall Street slide as gold and silver extend retreat
articles.summary: Hong Kong stocks fell on Wednesday, tracking weakness on Wall Street as a recent rally lost momentum, while gold and silver extended their pullback from record highs. The Hang Seng Index declined 0.7 per cent to 25,842.83 as of 10am local time. The Hang Seng Tech Index fell 1.2 per cent.
